\begin_layout Standard

\size normal
In a `first best' world, the principal knows 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

; he can therefore ask any quantity from the agent provided the agent accepts.
 Knowing the type 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 of the agent, the program of the principal is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
 & \underset{q,t}{\max}S(q)-t\\
\text{s.t. }t-\theta q & \geq0\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset

 The principal thus maximizes the following Lagrangian:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\underset{q,t}{\max}(S(q)-t)+\lambda(t-\theta q)
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 which is maximixed for 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
S^{\prime}(q)-\lambda\theta & =0\\
-1+\lambda & =0\nonumber \\
t-\theta q & =0
\end{align}

\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\lambda & =1\\
S^{\prime}(q) & =\theta\nonumber \\
t & =\theta q
\end{align}

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size normal
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda>0,$
\end_inset

 the rent left to either type is 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 so type 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 will be offered contract 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{H}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{H}-\theta_{H}q_{H}=0$
\end_inset

 while agent of type 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 will be offered contract 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{L}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{L}-\theta_{L}q_{L}=0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size normal
Given that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=1,$
\end_inset

 the objective of the principal is then:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size normal
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\underset{q}{\max}S(q)-\theta q
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size normal
When faced with an agent of type 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

, the principal will set 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{H}$
\end_inset

 s.t.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
S^{\prime}(q_{H})=\theta_{H}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 and when faced with an agent of type 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

, he will set 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{L}$
\end_inset

 s.t.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
S^{\prime}(q_{L})=\theta_{L}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

