 renege on a contract is even worse for the principal than in the case where
 there was inability to commit not to renegotiate: no contract can be signed
 with the agent and agents exert only the lowest effort level.
 The problem may be mitigated if rather than signing contract, the agent
 and the principal bargain after the state of nature is revealed.
 It may also be mitigated if the agent knows what is the state of nature
 before signing the contract and exerting effort.
 
\end_layout

